===message:Response #1  If I was 17-20 I don't think that I would want to know anything about huntingtons disease or whether I had it or not.  I feel like it would drag me down if I found out bad news and had it.  I probably wouldn't be as upbeat and might even feel sorry for myself.  I realize that maybe you would need to find out but I would rather face it later on in life when I absolutely had to.
Response #2 I think that all of these scenarios are selfish and demeaning to life.  It is great that we have people smart enough to figure out this kind of technology but cant they find something better to use their minds for. Each person is an individual with their own personality and characteristics.  I think that cloning is selfish, demeaning, and really just plain sick.  I wouldn't want anyone to be the same as me and I should have that right.
