===from:Denise Brekke
===date:Sun Jul 23 20:06:19 2000
===subject:homework 6
===message:Discussion 1:  If I had a parent with Huntington's Disease I would definately have myself tested.  I think always wondering would be harder than just facing up to the fact that I would die from it.  In the meantime I think I would probably spend some of my time doing some genetic testing trying to find a cure for myself and others.  Being a parent now I also know that if I had the disease I would have chossen not to have children.  I would not want to pass a life threatening disease on to anyone if I could avoid it.<BR>

Discussion 2:  For all of the given scenarios I would have to say that cloning is wrong.  Losing a loved pet is part of being a pet owner.  You shouldn't be able to replace the dog by cloning.  It would just be a dog that looked the same, it may not have the same tempermant.  I also don't think cloning a lost child is correct.  I feel that my kids are beautiful kids, but cloning them wouldn't bring them back to me.  They are who they are because of the experiences they have had and that we have shared.  You can't clone that.  You can't clone their heart and sole.  Albert Einstein was a great contributer to us, but there is another Einstein out there waiting to invent something even more spectatcular. Cloning should not be used to profit from a great basketball player either.  There has to be some moral issues involved when ever clonig is involved.
=========yorg=========
===from:Jodi Lloyd
===email:www.jlambert.iastate.edu
===date:Sun Jul 23 22:57:33 2000
===subject:Homework #6
===message:Topic #1

In such a situation, I would want to be tested  so that I would know whether or not I should reproduce.  I would not want to risk putting my unborn children through a tragic death just because I was afraid to know the truth about my end.  Besides, everyone is a ticking time bomb of death whether or not you carrying devasting genetic material.IF I knew, I could live the life I had been given with gusto and prepare myself and my family for the onset of the disease.

Topic #2

Like I've said before, death is inevitable and part of the human experience involves learning to accept Death's role in Life.  While losing a pet and especially a child can be devastating, what sort of truths about existance we have to formulate if we could simply "replace" our loved ones.  Death is part of the cycle of life and learning to deal with it part of our experience as emotional beings.  NOt only must we learn to cope with death, we also are given a  natural guarantee that we are genetically one-of-a-kind.  I'm not so sure it is humanity's place to rob individuals of the right of unique existance.  What sort of mental disorders are we going to breed into humans who know that they are the 3rd, 4th, etc clone of Mr. John Smith?  Cloning humans seems to cross bounds of human existance and integrity that I feel should not be crossed.        

=========yorg=========
===from:Gina Pighetti
===date:Mon Jul 24 16:17:09 2000
===subject:Hmk 6
===message:Topic #1
I think that I would want to be tested just so that I would know.  That way I would be ready for whatever was going to happen.  As well it would give me a head start on treatment, so as soon as the symptoms occur I would know exactly what was going on.  Finally I would be more aware of the studies going on to learn more about the disease.  If it was possible to participate in a study that could save my life I might be interested in doing it.

Topic #2
I do not believe that it is right to clone any type of living thing.   I don’t believe that any human has the right to play God.  There is a plan for each of us that God intended to be for a certain reason.  Who are we to play with that plan?  I understand the devastation of losing a loved one or pet, however who’s to say that this clone will be exactly like that the other one.  The personality traits could be very different, which could cause some grief.   Death is something that we have to accept as a part of life.  It is how our world as we know it is regulated.  If we were allowed to clone everything that we wanted the earth would soon have too many living things to support.

=========yorg=========
