===message:Discussion topic 1: Let us say that you are between the ages of 17-20 and one of your parents has Huntington's disease. Would you have yourself tested? 
I would.  I think it would be responsible for me to know if my kids could get the disease.  I would do everything possible to find a cure or promote the cause.  I would not feel discouraged or sentenced, but I would make the best of the years I have to live.

Discussion topic 2: Consider the following scenarios and say whether you think cloning would be justified. 

Scenario 1: Would you clone your dead pet? No

Scenario 2: Would you clone your 5-year-old child who has been hit by a car and killed? No

Scenario 3: Would you support cloning Albert Einstein? No

Scenario 4: Should an entrepreneur be allowed to clone Michael Jordon? No.

I think clonning is not justified in any case.  Each individual is original and unique.  Even for those who don't believe in the existence of soul, it is evident that identical twins raised in the same family are not identical in their personalities.

I have five kids and they are definitely not replaceable.  Each of them is unique.  If one of them is not anymore with me, his soul would not be here anymore.
=========yorg=========
