===message:#1 - I would have myself tested for Huntington's disease because I would like to have the opportunity to live my life to the fullest.  By being slightly aware of your future in life you can do things when they are first presented to you instead of saying, "well, maybe next time."  I think it would also aid in paying attention to the conditions my parent ould be going through so i could have some idea what I was in for in the future.

#2 - I think I cna answer this question and all of its scenerios in one blanket statement that I think cloning for any reason is wrong.  I wuld definitely not clone any sort of animal because although it would be great to have a "dog" that lived forever people need to know that life shouldn't be like that.  The idea of cloning a loved one is also wrong because althoguh it is truely unfortunate that anyone would die so young the world would become overpopulated if people lived forever.  People should also not be cloned if they have a special skill like Einstein or Michael Jordan, if theose people were cloned then "once-in-a-lifetime" events would never happen because the people who created them would just keep doing them over and over.
