===from:Larry Iseminger
===email:larryiseminger@hotmail.com
===date:Wed Aug  2 22:28:08 2000
===subject:Homework #6
===message:1) Carpe Diem - Seize the day  -  It may be very cliche, but I think that we should all strive to follow this simple message.  No matter what, I would not be tested. Even before marriage and having children I don't think I would test myself.  We should strive to live each day to the fullest... each day we offer new things to the world. Once a person reaches the 30-40 year old mark, there may be a cure.  In fact, before reaching 30 or 40 a person with the disease may be the one to discover the cure.  We should never underestimate ourselves- especially with a special condition such as Huntington's disease.

2) Taking into consideration the 4 different scenarios-  I would NOT clone any human.  The same goes for pets.  I don't believe it is just the person or pet, it is the emotional bond - the personality that is important.  It doesn't matter whether the person is the same or not, the emotional side of a being will never be the same.  You can never replace something once it's gone.  Sure-  you may replace it physically, but the spirit of the person, pet, or object will never be the exact same.
=========yorg=========
